UN Says Climate Talks Making Progress on Adaptation Measures

-- B y   R e e d   L a n d b e r g
-- 
2011-12-02T11:30:14Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-12-02/un-says-climate-talks-making-progress-on-adaptation-measures.html
Envoys at United Nations climate
talks are likely to agree a series of measures helping nations
adapt to global warming, according to the diplomat leading
talks.  Christiana Figueres, executive secretary of the UN
Framework on  Climate Change , said the measures will be included
in a draft text of “a least 100 pages” suggesting conclusions
from the meeting in Durban,  South Africa . The text will be
issued tomorrow. The meeting finishes on Dec. 9.  “We will see a good decision on adaptation plans,” she
said. “Durban will move forward with adaptation.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Reed Landberg at 
 landberg@bloomberg.net  